        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 1:54PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 152 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sardis, or 12 miles southwest of Florence, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Florence, Timmonsville, Sardis, Effingham, Friendfield, New Hope,
Evergreen, Coward, Olanta, Carolinas Hospital System, and Carolinas
Hospital System - Cedar Tower.

This includes Interstate 95 in South Carolina between mile markers
147 and 156.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
